data.Title: NSLOCTEXT("[D0FC0897491D3AFE01A775B2C7AEEA93]", "04D944D54F725BB7044DAF94943FBAE2", "Story of the Lowlands")
data.Description:
NSLOCTEXT("[D0FC0897491D3AFE01A775B2C7AEEA93]", "DDC27B144AAAFFDE11ACC2AE927FE283", "The Lowlands are the poorest of the five regions and one of the oldest, its occupants relying mainly on agriculture for their livelihood. Due to the scourge the people are barely producing enough to feed themselves, let alone sell.

The current controlling lord, Ashbourne, is cruel and frequently raises the already high taxes above what the Queen orders, taking a generous cut for himself.

It was once a beautiful, flourishing place, but years of hardship are now beginning to show throughout the villages, some more than others.")

data.Title: NSLOCTEXT("[5B877BF2F01CFAFF8E382B89FD5C5408]", "AB11EFB74148A7F1DC9092AFF58B1C76", "Bradford")
data.Description: NSLOCTEXT("[5B877BF2F01CFAFF8E382B89FD5C5408]", "41368909435ED67EA73AF0A09CC65E58", "Bradford is a young village located between the woods and a stream. It was founded by travelers from other regions in Karvenia. The brother of Padstow\'s Elder, Franciszek, and his partner Andrea chose the location, as it seemed ideal for hunting and gathering herbs.\r\n\r\nAfter working with a neighboring village to craft bows and arrows, the Elders of each village decided to merge their people, and Bradford was established. The new village flourished through the sale of meat and other byproducts from their hunts.")

data.Title: NSLOCTEXT("[ACEE6ACBB16D540280078AA6BC0F43E2]", "4F4150DF421F8F1A0A83D1A29D7EA12A", "Crasmere")
data.Description: NSLOCTEXT("[ACEE6ACBB16D540280078AA6BC0F43E2]", "2C72A1474F66A278D0E7D98FDF359771", "Crasmere, a young village born from a fishing camp, thrived as its residents aspired to build a prosperous community. The village\'s primary source of income stemmed from the bustling fishing market, attracting various individuals from the Lowlands, Highlands and other regions of Karvenia.")

data.Title: NSLOCTEXT("[1574F58F8E398E913A104BC702F3CC3B]", "14FF8B354AEBD8E6BD5758A982F54199", "Haerndean village")
data.Description: NSLOCTEXT("[1574F58F8E398E913A104BC702F3CC3B]", "C46987524E2C48C29218E69DEF823D7C", "Haerndean is the oldest village in the Lowlands, settled by proud and independent people seeking fertile land and freedom. Despite limited prosperity, Haerndean remained peaceful, living off the land with basic tools.\r\n\r\nWhen the first Lord of the Lowlands, a man named Robert Copue, arrived in the region, Haerndean strongly opposed collaborating with authority. This ultimately led to a rift with the neighboring village of Horndean, and animosity between the two villages still persists to this day.")

data.Title: NSLOCTEXT("[A0386154E53A8F1928D1399997D513DE]", "0D1A4B1B419D09B4A556ED863C3040B8", "Horndean")
data.Description: NSLOCTEXT("[A0386154E53A8F1928D1399997D513DE]", "AE25716F4A2F4F45D9D225A569DBD225", "Haerndean and Horndean are two villages with contrasting histories and traditions. Horndean was founded by the oldest clan in the Lowlands, who sought a peaceful life near a stream where they could fish and mine for iron. However, years of loyalty to the monarchy and overuse of iron resources caused the stream to dry up, leaving the people to face this hardship alone.\r\n\r\nWhile Horndean became a village loyal to the monarchy, Haerndean remained proud of its free heritage and traditions. Over time, due to oppression, Horndean\'s support for the Queen waned to the point where the people are now ready to rebel. Unfortunately, even with a shared desire for change, relations between the two clans never improved.")

data.Title: NSLOCTEXT("[4EC4DAF497AD72060BEB27104CDDF90E]", "8FF26B04471F3EE1AF3C8183C4FB0ED3", "Pagan Altar near Blackridgepool")
data.Description: NSLOCTEXT("[4EC4DAF497AD72060BEB27104CDDF90E]", "EBFD261D48E187D6CC787FB1ED81588D", "We will never make demands of you in your Divinity.\r\nWe will gladly accept all you are willing to give, be it punishment or prosperity.\r\nWe will not let time claim you as it claims us.")

data.Title: NSLOCTEXT("[AEEA281F84389923249452345ABCED54]", "FA0190824C76138D53E4F78182ACADBF", "Pagan Shrine near Crasmere")
data.Description: NSLOCTEXT("[AEEA281F84389923249452345ABCED54]", "30242DD64B8928868AF8D6BA23871F03", "May the seas be calm, our nets strong, and the catch abundant.")

data.Title: NSLOCTEXT("[1FBE69CB74A1F1E36F25216AD21C2569]", "31944415406B37CCC3176E9BAC62960E", "Pagan Shrine near Farnworth")
data.Description: NSLOCTEXT("[1FBE69CB74A1F1E36F25216AD21C2569]", "4A9E34CA4B8EB0FD8D5633A115137564", "Devannos, hear us! Your hand alone is that which guides our arrows. Let them strike true so that we may spill blood upon the ground in your honor.")

data.Title: NSLOCTEXT("[F6EE2CC1311550744B350DA72318E92E]", "CE697BCD45902CC9B07B7BA23CDA864D", "Pagan Shrine near Padstow")
data.Description: NSLOCTEXT("[F6EE2CC1311550744B350DA72318E92E]", "05B38C7847B5018C47FA3D9185FE2B96", "Bless us, O Feared Gods. May your altar overflow with bounty, just like our lands. Protect our people, bring hope for better mornings, till the blood pours from our veins or death will take us back home.")

data.Title: NSLOCTEXT("[DDB61DA3FC8F9F76AE19D6E9B0F44E57]", "006D7E964B638614D7524289BFB86FD9", "Chapter 7: Crasmere")
data.Description: NSLOCTEXT("[DDB61DA3FC8F9F76AE19D6E9B0F44E57]", "13203AFF45303F368C0983AAF91FE0BA", "Crasmere was established just five years ago, and thus has no history. But we wish them all the best in their future endeavors.")

data.Title: NSLOCTEXT("[EC6BD1DC5E795B61342FE858A5D9F858]", "DA871B94443B169A9E00C2825C2845AB", "Last Words of Bellwright")
data.Description:
NSLOCTEXT("[EC6BD1DC5E795B61342FE858A5D9F858]", "0D5ED58F44C2BBD3B485989833B8D5B6", "I am the caretaker of this belltower, entrusted with its maintenance and protection. My duty has been to ensure that the bell atop this tower serves its purpose: to warn the people of Northern Descent and neighboring villages of impending danger.

For years, I have stood watch over this land from the heights of this tower. It has been my responsibility to keep the bell in working order, ready to ring out its warning at the first sign of trouble. But now, as I pen these words, the tower lies in ruins around me, a testament to the passage of time and the neglect of our once-vigilant community.

I write this note in the hopes that someone will stumble upon it and learn from our mistakes. Our failure to maintain this belltower has left us vulnerable to the dangers that now threaten to engulf us. I can only pray that whoever finds this note will take up the mantle of responsibility and restore this tower to its former glory.

May this belltower once again serve as a beacon of warning, guiding the people of The Lowlands through the storms that lie ahead.")

data.Title: NSLOCTEXT("[1C4A85C59A07528E735714D27AA68B86]", "71E0AF4C40BE576EECAFB1BF31F34C9C", "Daughter diary")
data.Description: NSLOCTEXT("[1C4A85C59A07528E735714D27AA68B86]", "F35C48284F0AEDE4BD690AB8F3B07126", "I don\'t know how long I\'m going to live. I miss my home and my father. I feel like it\'s my last day. They left me alone, without water and food. It\'s my last wish if someone finds this letter, please let my father know about my fate. Tell him that I love him so much.")

data.Title: NSLOCTEXT("[89D980B574075D95CFD544BDEA820326]", "A35326D843B341125CBA169CCCF05965", "Killer\'s Journal Note 1")
data.Description: NSLOCTEXT("[89D980B574075D95CFD544BDEA820326]", "2EF5A8A04A6AFDFC6398A49C4F5677D7", "I have been shown the light by the spirit of my ancestor. I will follow in his footsteps, and put an end to the heresy that is rampant in this land. It is my duty.")

data.Title: NSLOCTEXT("[89985B6A63D0133B2422D5EAF3138B5B]", "5BE5D80A4E731190542C45ACA662C1AD", "Letter from Lord Ashbourne")
data.Description:
NSLOCTEXT("[89985B6A63D0133B2422D5EAF3138B5B]", "0F34D1AE444B0D7FFD2BB39378C36DF0", "To the Golden Child of the Lowlands,

Congratulations on liberating so many villages, and releasing the peasants from their perceived shackles! Truly an incredible achievement. I hope it was worth it.

It crossed my mind recently how truly absurd it is that we have never met. Me, as the Lord of the Lowlands, and you, its brave, new savior.

So I would like to cordially invite you to a luncheon in my castle to discuss the future of the Lowlands, as well as the ongoing problems being caused by those damn bandit groups.

I look forward to finally meeting you.

Yours Royally,

Lord Edmund Ashbourne III.")

data.Title: NSLOCTEXT("[F3AD3BC43AC334A6AE2763F93AA272B3]", "A224E7B14BD54ED738D98E93608C01AA", "Notice of Tax Increase")
data.Description:
NSLOCTEXT("[F3AD3BC43AC334A6AE2763F93AA272B3]", "5343AB7040A83DBF615A4F936BCE10AA", "To all tax-payers of the Lowlands,

Her Highness Queen Osenne has degreed a new tax rate of 45% for all Karvenian serfs, replacing the previous tax rate of 30%. This new tax rate is in effect immediately, and all serfs will have 30 days to submit their first taxation at the updated rate, which must be given to the tax collector assigned to your locality.

Failure to pay the correct amount of tax is punishable by fines, imprisonment and, in the case of repeat offenses, death.

Signed,
Lord Ashbourne.")

data.Title: NSLOCTEXT("[656313D1030FC537365D5D0097411313]", "16AEF00044404173F7D56D87749ADAD3", "Brigand\'s note")
data.Description: NSLOCTEXT("[656313D1030FC537365D5D0097411313]", "87DABEB14C72EDFE6EBBFEA3FF78F2A2", "Those Red Thorns, dirty bandits. Took that smuggler caravan right out from under us. Getting the mole inside was expensive, now Ashbourne is going to be mad. But we can fix it if we find the hostages they took.")

data.Title: NSLOCTEXT("[E9528AA750DC3AF2CFE48665ECA80A52]", "499654F849F57277045EC4A432626A75", "Scam Letter")
data.Description:
NSLOCTEXT("[E9528AA750DC3AF2CFE48665ECA80A52]", "6B17C95C4C9B7B0F326A63A7665615DA", "My friend,

I am a wealthy prospector from Aldekerk, with an exciting business proposition for you. I have recently been told about a silver mine in the Lowlands, waiting to be tapped. I would be delighted to share all profits with you.

However, I am required to pay to open the mine for silver extraction. And if we are going to be business partners, I will need your help with these fees. Please send 200 gold to the return address. I look forward to a prosperous and profitable business partnership.

Kind regards,
Jonathan Spengle")

data.Title: NSLOCTEXT("[829D7E6B270C8E43B84C08D3803D92B8]", "10EC7B574F0CB292E17E7D96D938DA82", "Torn Piece of Paper")
data.Description:
NSLOCTEXT("[829D7E6B270C8E43B84C08D3803D92B8]", "379F59AE48B45B39745644903E72C78C", "...We're fighting to save these innocents, but it's getting harder by the day.
Who could have known that The Butcher, with that grim name, is someone who's got a soft spot for kids. Together, we're a makeshift family in this mess.
But there's talk of a rat among us. Someone leaking our next moves, maybe even leading the king's dogs to our door. Can't trust anyone these days.
And then there's my own kid. Always looking at me like they know something's up. Makes my skin crawl. I'm in this to protect them, but how do you shield your own from a storm like this?
Every move we make feels like a gamble. But we're in too deep now to turn back...")

data.Title: NSLOCTEXT("[1330EEA1D91BC1C9CEC5CF4980B8D2AA]", "32269FF243A238CDAB09CF8E08A04720", "The dead bodies of missing Villagers")
data.Description: NSLOCTEXT("[1330EEA1D91BC1C9CEC5CF4980B8D2AA]", "56D645704AE32CB347BE8F80AF2EE3EE", "They were unlucky, this forest is full of wolves...")

data.Title: NSLOCTEXT("[ADB6E7ACDA167E84147A0F891C54D3F7]", "9679A04741C3B3781DE2648136887099", "Lydia Simic Note")
data.Description: NSLOCTEXT("[ADB6E7ACDA167E84147A0F891C54D3F7]", "1688526A47B80A1F1E1D3187B502A6F5", "Let this be my message: I do not suffer traitors, nor those who shelter them. Even my own blood cannot escape me.")

data.Title: NSLOCTEXT("[418CDCD43089E559E5E0A44A34B4ECD6]", "2D15CAF74C7EA2D2E5D78CB1FBE0A5BA", "Warning letter demanding a book be removed")
data.Description:
NSLOCTEXT("[418CDCD43089E559E5E0A44A34B4ECD6]", "2517322843B4E9CDEC36058F8F553018", "To the Business Owner,

It has come to our attention that you are stocking and selling copies of a book that has been officially banned by the order of Queen Osenne. The book in question is called The Heroes of the Rebellion, and has been made forbidden in Karvenia due to its pro-rebellion propaganda and anti-monarchy rhetoric.

You have 48 hours to remove the book from your stock, or we will send guards to remove it.

Yours with kindness,
Lord A. Paltar III, Royal Advisor")

data.Title: NSLOCTEXT("[053348B63F3310C1DB8598F967ECB1D4]", "E7B69B0C47B8D5B608298AB87332C696", "Garrick\'s Letter")
data.Description: NSLOCTEXT("[053348B63F3310C1DB8598F967ECB1D4]", "9183B5044AF8F1B78EA6D3BCA8FA59DA", "Near the Salt Eye, for a bit of fun.")

data.Title: NSLOCTEXT("[D2CA077506281C5BDCA631329468FE82]", "F6474A144D652DEE1895E68B49AF583A", "Sigil Clue: Haerdean")
data.Description: NSLOCTEXT("[D2CA077506281C5BDCA631329468FE82]", "EAF2907D4B0A53BF511C15A6F5B22D39", "Ketyl Simmonds saw the sigil on a finely made black cloak sold to him by a stranger. Two well-behaved Brigands later bought the cloak from him for a high price.")

data.Title: NSLOCTEXT("[4B9AA13079C0D25B241B5503624E7A9B]", "90B5ECCA4F55B3F4EF19A390C28B4D70", "Chronicle of the Isles")
data.Description: NSLOCTEXT("[4B9AA13079C0D25B241B5503624E7A9B]", "F9BBFDD24CF38F6564BA65BAEB6DE0A3", "Man claims that he can speak with animals - upon further investigation, it was discovered he just drank too much Doll\'s Tears. A new side effect of the drink.")

data.Title: NSLOCTEXT("[071CE1C1A38D6959BB24C974204D2295]", "412A5E1C43233A31D9B8B290DB489C62", "Cult Leader Note")
data.Description: NSLOCTEXT("[071CE1C1A38D6959BB24C974204D2295]", "16DDA21741FA38EE47153784A8B3C461", "The Overseer\'s influence spreads far beyond this single node. Seek the crimson star when it aligns, and the next phase shall begin. The non-believers will tremble before our ultimate revelation.")

data.Title: NSLOCTEXT("[6A0EF006AECB098A4B402DF847A456D3]", "924F1903466CD4557759FCB643C2FA0E", "Cult Invitation")
data.Description: NSLOCTEXT("[6A0EF006AECB098A4B402DF847A456D3]", "BE0ED388402610807A789EAAC0ACE75D", "To the worthy initiate, you are summoned to the Sanctum of the Overseer. Your dedication has not gone unnoticed. Come to the ancient oak at midnight on the next new moon. The path to enlightenment awaits.")

data.Title: NSLOCTEXT("[86C93C338446BD92B62C8DE4C56B398D]", "2FD64317491A603EE309E4A57938B927", "Weird Altar")
data.Description: NSLOCTEXT("[86C93C338446BD92B62C8DE4C56B398D]", "8F858F55424CBF781ED9B0BB6CFE06CD", "Wip")

data.Title: NSLOCTEXT("[5EA90B94C6A1E0941DA481E42383463B]", "093F99F247D58BF2BC6B8CBBE69AEB54", "Bradford Election is Close!")
data.Description:
NSLOCTEXT("[5EA90B94C6A1E0941DA481E42383463B]", "8FFBF79446D1384ACFA21F85CC6957AD", "People of the Lowlands,

It is with great import that we announce the upcoming election for the position of our esteemed Elder in Village Bradford. One of the candidates for this vital role is none other than our current Elder, Patryk Sten, who is known for his courage and wisdom, vying for your vote against his electoral opposition.

Candidates, express your noble intentions at the village square, the heart of our community. Your voices will be heard when the time is right.

This pivotal decision will carve the destiny of our beloved Bradford. Spread this message across The Lowlands, let every villager know about it.

In unity,
The Council of Great Lord Ashbourn, ruler of the Lowlands.")

data.Title: NSLOCTEXT("[39A85690FD35063A6F19C339DBD97D6A]", "6118F60D4491A25C263E179661BA8FD5", "The Butcher a Traitor")
data.Description:
NSLOCTEXT("[39A85690FD35063A6F19C339DBD97D6A]", "B0C7C6984C9F3DD7FA62B985D4BB84E9", "Attention, inhabitants of the realm!

A shadow looms over our land, cast by the sinister presence of THE BUTCHER. This vile predator preys upon our villages, kidnapping innocent souls without mercy or remorse.

His actions are a blight upon our kingdom, his cruelty unmatched. Families are torn asunder, communities left in fear and despair as he continues his reign of terror unchecked.

Remain vigilant, dear citizens, and report any sightings of THE BUTCHER to the authorities. Let us stand together against this despicable menace and protect our people from his wicked schemes.

By decree of the crown and Lord Ashbourne. Dead or alive, The Butcher needs to be punished for his crimes against our realm.")

data.Title: NSLOCTEXT("[5E4A50AF1830F89FE64B4B827514F040]", "BA3266E04BA5EFB2A658D5AA99661334", "Solstice")
data.Description:
NSLOCTEXT("[5E4A50AF1830F89FE64B4B827514F040]", "2E62B6AB4CC4BE5B7F9DA690B9C50996", "Denizens of The Lowlands!

The grand Solstice doth draw nigh, and with it, the esteemed Lord Ashbourne extends a heartfelt invitation to a celebration of momentous proportions. Distinguished guests from the farthest reaches of Karvenia shall grace our beloved lands, gathering under the watchful eyes of our noble Lord.

In anticipation of this auspicious occasion, a decree resonates from the very heart of Ashbourne: let cleanliness be our guiding virtue. May thine homes gleam with pristine splendor, villages sparkle like stars in the night, and thyself be cleansed with the utmost diligence. Pray, keep thy animals at a distance, ensuring the festivities unfold without disruption.

Be forewarned, for those who neglect these solemn instructions shall face dire consequences. In his wisdom, Lord Ashbourne hath decreed that only those who uphold the sanctity of cleanliness shall partake in the joyous revelry. Those who dare to transgress shall bear the weight of punishment, serving as a solemn reminder that in Ashbourne, order and decorum reign supreme.

As the grand Solstice casts its radiant glow upon our lands, let Ashbourne stand as a beacon of grace and distinction in the eyes of all who gather from across the realm. May the festivities be blessed, and the spirit of unity prevail in our cherished home.

Signed,
Lieutenant Berthold Kug.")

data.Title: NSLOCTEXT("[B1F3AA40D7E9E96DEB16CBB847E19C4E]", "5FF91B324FB0CD033766089226A630A5", "Taxes for Safety")
data.Description:
NSLOCTEXT("[B1F3AA40D7E9E96DEB16CBB847E19C4E]", "7C713ED14AFCED203F187D95C1B3CF42", "To all tax-payers of the Lowlands,

Lord Ashbourne, in his noble wisdom, calls for a modest increase in contributions to the community. Fear not, for these coins shall blossom into citadels, walls, and bridges, fortifying our realm against adversity. Rejoice, as prosperity dawns under the benevolent gaze of the Lord of the Lowlands!

Signed,
The Council of Great Lord Ashbourn.")

data.Title: NSLOCTEXT("[CA2F9156D090B4F5F527D7F21B05C6F2]", "B89F556A41B25CC9B315FDAE9368A938", "Threat and Heroism")
data.Description:
NSLOCTEXT("[CA2F9156D090B4F5F527D7F21B05C6F2]", "3662A9424121D1257788A9AB5ACF9D75", "Denizens of The Lowlands!

With great pride and admiration, we declare that the once-menacing specter of banditry has been vanquished from our lands, thanks to the resolute efforts of our noble Lord Ashbourne. By the royal decree of Queen Ossene, Lord Ashbourne took up the mantle of protector, leading our brave forces against the marauding bandits that once plagued our kingdom. Through strategic brilliance and unyielding courage, these outlaws have been scattered to the winds, and their threat extinguished like a flickering flame.

Signed,
The Council of the Great Lord Ashbourne.")

data.Title: NSLOCTEXT("[7F3F5D97D5FF65379D2933E6DC6EBD19]", "7E1E086B48CFE23B614911AEEF33F503", "Wolves!")
data.Description:
NSLOCTEXT("[7F3F5D97D5FF65379D2933E6DC6EBD19]", "B9B1EA0A40D387017B80798F3CAEB9E2", "Residents,

A pack of wolves has been sighted in our community, posing a threat to both villagers and livestock. Please stay vigilant and avoid traveling alone, especially at dusk. Skilled hunters needed to assist. Everyone who believes they can handle the challenge, please volunteer to Elder Dobron to fight these beasts.

Signed,
Elder Dobron Yorklyn.")

data.Title: NSLOCTEXT("[950E7C51C5EB07AC1F4C7892FF454E23]", "871246DA41877D26740E56B6F1929286", "Royal Bastards Journal Entry 3")
data.Description: NSLOCTEXT("[950E7C51C5EB07AC1F4C7892FF454E23]", "8D23A3EC49CD7F602DA7B5A516743DF0", "Damn, those Brigands, royal lapdogs took two of us. We have to attack them by surprise, even if we are better trained and experienced they have numbers and fresh equipment. Mildred told us just to avoid them, maybe he was right.")

data.Title: NSLOCTEXT("[E1F3AB94D55388EB14962EC04B599DBC]", "E8F20DE9470FECC7DD4FD7A52C0DB1CB", "Guidance of Lord Ashbourne!")
data.Description:
NSLOCTEXT("[E1F3AB94D55388EB14962EC04B599DBC]", "610550354CA25F4721B952AD5162BA99", "Resilient Farmers of Blackridgepool!

Under the steadfast guidance of Lord Ashbourne, our protector and leader, we thrive amidst the fields of Blackridgepool. His unwavering courage and tireless commitment ensure our prosperity.

Lord Ashbourne's recent triumph in repelling threats to our land stands as a testament to his strength and leadership. Embedded in our history, he epitomizes bravery and resilience, guiding us through challenges with unwavering resolve.

Let us honor Lord Ashbourne's valor and dedication, ensuring his name echoes through Blackridgepool's proud farming legacy.
Long live Lord Ashbourne! May his legacy endure, a beacon of resilience and unity!

In unity,
The Council of Great Lord Ashbourne.")

data.Title: NSLOCTEXT("[370E38801CC8993133EAB5F9A02729F1]", "039B61FF4A88EB08030300B584ED5606", "Bradford Election")
data.Description:
NSLOCTEXT("[370E38801CC8993133EAB5F9A02729F1]", "8F75A5EE4ABC9637B0BFF39786C9B9E0", "Noble Denizens of Blackridgepool,

By the decree of the Council, under the vigilant eye of Great Lord Ashbourne, we herald the forthcoming election to appoint the Elder in the Village of Bradford. Among the contenders for this esteemed role stands our current Elder, Patryk Sten, revered for his unwavering resolve and sage counsel.

It is with great import that we beseech thee, esteemed denizens of Blackridgepool, to heed this call to arms. Let this decree echo through every furrow and field, ensuring that each of these comprehends the profound significance of this decision that shall shape the destiny of our beloved land.

In unity,
The Council of Great Lord Ashbourne.")

data.Title: NSLOCTEXT("[361AF4F300A05C3E67CDEAD58ACEE58B]", "66F385C14767EDC4B1AFD085C9AF3AC2", "Wheat Taxes")
data.Description:
NSLOCTEXT("[361AF4F300A05C3E67CDEAD58ACEE58B]", "4D596C1743D22AF1962A4880E94D8510", "Esteemed farmers of Blackridgepool,

In accordance with the directives of the Council of Great Lord Ashbourne, we bring forth a proclamation concerning a revision in tax rates, effective immediately, to foster the prosperity and welfare of our esteemed farming village.

Farmers shall contribute a portion of their harvest, reflective of their esteemed profession. These funds will be allocated towards the maintenance of farmlands, the procurement of essential resources, and the fortification of our village's defenses against external adversaries.

Your adherence to these tax obligations is crucial for the continued growth and security of Blackridgepool. Rest assured, every contribution will be utilized judiciously to safeguard our way of life and ensure a prosperous future for all who call Blackridgepool home.

With gratitude for your cooperation,
The Council of Great Lord Ashbourne.")

data.Title: NSLOCTEXT("[ADD5B84F53A214A4494099E839BEBF67]", "B6061B3340E619A5EF45CA91BA2972E5", "Dangerous Individual Beware!")
data.Description:
NSLOCTEXT("[ADD5B84F53A214A4494099E839BEBF67]", "BCDA704F4CF03D476A655285E16CA079", "Citizens of the realm!

Beware! A shadow lurks amongst us, a figure known only as THE BUTCHER. This vile traitor of the crown and Lord Ashbourne has stained our land with the blood of the innocent. With his own hands, he has snuffed out lives in fits of rage and fury.

But fear not, for we shall not rest until this menace is brought to justice! We call upon the brave souls of our kingdom to keep watch and be vigilant. If you should lay eyes upon this wretched fiend, do not approach him. Instead, swiftly inform the brigands of his whereabouts.

Together, we shall root out this treachery and restore peace to our land. Let the name of THE BUTCHER be known to all, and may he be brought to justice swiftly!

In unity,
The Council of Great Lord Ashbourne.")

data.Title: NSLOCTEXT("[9DA44E51CD57190A27421052B6E248D6]", "F253AE43494581830C035380853F2140", "Solstice")
data.Description:
NSLOCTEXT("[9DA44E51CD57190A27421052B6E248D6]", "5E33CB6C4F3C38B164B9C8907719497B", "Denizens of The Lowlands!

The grand Solstice doth draw nigh, and with it, the esteemed Lord Ashbourne extends a heartfelt invitation to a celebration of momentous proportions. Distinguished guests from the farthest reaches of Karvenia shall grace our beloved lands, gathering under the watchful eyes of our noble Lord.

In anticipation of this auspicious occasion, a decree resonates from the very heart of Ashbourne: let cleanliness be our guiding virtue. May thine homes gleam with pristine splendor, villages sparkle like stars in the night, and thyself be cleansed with the utmost diligence. Pray, keep thy animals at a distance, ensuring the festivities unfold without disruption.

Be forewarned, for those who neglect these solemn instructions shall face dire consequences. In his wisdom, Lord Ashbourne hath decreed that only those who uphold the sanctity of cleanliness shall partake in the joyous revelry. Those who dare to transgress shall bear the weight of punishment, serving as a solemn reminder that in Ashbourne, order and decorum reign supreme.

As the grand Solstice casts its radiant glow upon our lands, let Ashbourne stand as a beacon of grace and distinction in the eyes of all who gather from across the realm. May the festivities be blessed, and the spirit of unity prevail in our cherished home.

Signed,
Lieutenant Berthold Kug.")

data.Title: NSLOCTEXT("[2BFA9D4C3FFE2F368F211C5A665B7CC4]", "E439781847D774AA58AE5FAC29E46903", "New Taxes")
data.Description:
NSLOCTEXT("[2BFA9D4C3FFE2F368F211C5A665B7CC4]", "12966EA24FC73D39EE51F9ABA0D72051", "Denizens of Bradford,

In accordance with the decrees of the Council of Great Lord Ashbourne, we hereby proclaim an adjustment in tax rates, effective immediately, to fortify the prosperity of our esteemed village. The revenues collected shall be directed towards vital services and infrastructure development, tailored to the needs of our skilled hunters and trappers.

Hunters shall contribute a portion of their game, while trappers shall provide a percentage of their furs. These funds will be allocated towards the maintenance of hunting grounds, the procurement of essential supplies, and the fortification of our village defenses against external threats.

Your compliance with these tax obligations, reflective of your esteemed profession, is essential for the continued growth and security of Bradford.

Rest assured, every contribution will be utilized judiciously to safeguard our way of life and ensure a thriving future for all who call Bradford home.

In unity,
The Council of Great Lord Ashbourne.")

data.Title: NSLOCTEXT("[BBEB566DEE33DB80348600200134C539]", "E6AD810943FCE4F0401833AE106A030D", "Great Lord Ashbourne!")
data.Description:
NSLOCTEXT("[BBEB566DEE33DB80348600200134C539]", "1B58777643DA989D67CC3DB4CDA258DE", "Brave Hunters of Bradford!

In the heart of the wild, amidst the echoing calls of the forest, stands our valiant leader, Lord Ashbourne, a stalwart defender of our territory and way of life. Let your spirits rise with pride as we honor his unwavering courage and tireless dedication to our beloved Bradford.

Lord Ashbourne, a beacon of strength and resilience, has led countless battles to safeguard our borders and preserve our hunting grounds. His recent triumph in repelling a fierce incursion from our adversaries speaks volumes of his strategic prowess and unwavering resolve.

Deeply ingrained in the annals of Bradford's history, Lord Ashbourne is the epitome of bravery and leadership. From leading daring hunts to ensuring the prosperity of our community, he remains our unwavering protector and guide.

Let us raise our voices in praise and gratitude for Lord Ashbourne, whose bravery knows no bounds and whose commitment inspires us all. May his legacy endure for generations to come, a testament to the indomitable spirit of our people.

Long live Lord Ashbourne! May his name be forever etched in the annals of our proud hunters' heritage!

In unity,
The Council of Great Lord Ashbourne.")

data.Title: NSLOCTEXT("[7BE5AE84850FD1D50F7C980B9408D10E]", "0C49C0F6453B552F5856978449B4ABC4", "Long live Lord Ashbourne!")
data.Description:
NSLOCTEXT("[7BE5AE84850FD1D50F7C980B9408D10E]", "CB9DC25A4497794FE8B834B12AE2A0FF", "Resilient people of Crasmere!

Along the shores of Crasmere, where the gentle lapping of waves meets the bustling rhythm of the fishing boats, we stand united under the auspicious leadership of Lord Ashbourne, our steadfast protector and advocate. Let us extol his tireless efforts, which have brought prosperity and abundance to our humble village.

Lord Ashbourne, a beacon of strength and foresight, has spearheaded initiatives to bolster our fishing industry and enhance our village's vitality. Through his leadership, Crasmere has flourished, with plentiful catches sustaining our community and fostering a sense of camaraderie among our fishermen.

Embedded in the fabric of Crasmere's identity, Lord Ashbourne symbolizes unity and prosperity. His unwavering dedication has transformed our village into a beacon of hope and resilience along the coastal shores.

Let us raise our voices in gratitude and admiration for Lord Ashbourne, whose vision and leadership have brought unprecedented blessings to Crasmere. May his legacy of progress and prosperity endure for generations to come, a testament to the strength and unity of our fishing village.

Long live Lord Ashbourne! May his guiding light continue to enrich the lives of all who call Crasmere home!

In unity,
The Council of Great Lord Ashbourne.")

data.Title: NSLOCTEXT("[AAC22E793CD5B2A582A8E585937FE3D5]", "A6BF433646559CF16239FB8772990CEC", "Election in Bradford!")
data.Description:
NSLOCTEXT("[AAC22E793CD5B2A582A8E585937FE3D5]", "7B1F6AD142E2B018FCCFDC826160D572", "People of Crasmere,

NSLOCTEXT("[575C4247A994B4628451F73B50D94046]", "8A91D8E24791E7762DE2A3A1159E798A", "Esteemed Fishermen and Citizens of Crasmere,

These funds will be allocated towards the maintenance of our harbor, the acquisition of necessary supplies, and the fortification of our village's defenses against external threats.

Your compliance with these tax obligations is essential for the continued growth and security of Crasmere. Rest assured, every contribution will be utilized judiciously to safeguard our way of life and ensure a prosperous future for all who call Crasmere home.

In unity,
The Council of Great Lord Ashbourne.")

data.Title: NSLOCTEXT("[0EAB50228E4E0C731EAB22637C205309]", "61AB8AC34A924A2A78DF1FB6BCC979C1", "The Great Deeds of the Lord")
data.Description:
NSLOCTEXT("[0EAB50228E4E0C731EAB22637C205309]", "148282234D2F03D4356C4DB33EB741AD", "People of Padstow!

Great Lord Ashbourne, unwavering in bravery and unmatched in merit, stands as a beacon of strength and loyalty to our land. Let pride fill your hearts as you recall his countless deeds and sacrifices for our community.

Recently, Lord Ashbourne led a daring expedition to repel a bandit raid on our village, bravely confronting the threat and ensuring the safety of our people. His heroic actions in the face of danger are a testament to his unwavering commitment to our protection.

Lord Ashbourne, deeply rooted in our village's history, defended our land with unwavering courage. From securing borders to guiding us through trials, he remains a steadfast guardian of our dreams.

His bravery knows no bounds, his dedication a model for us all. Let pride swell as we behold his banner, bringing tidings of peace and prosperity.

Long live Lord Ashbourne! May his legacy endure in our hearts! May pride always adorn the Padstow board as a symbol of our gratitude and respect for our esteemed leader.

In unity,
The Council of Great Lord Ashbourne.")

data.Title: NSLOCTEXT("[DCB092BB47CEBDF47F2EDD3AB49B4177]", "2136C9E640FAAC1D6ED8A2AD39073052", "Choice of Tomorrow!")
data.Description:
NSLOCTEXT("[DCB092BB47CEBDF47F2EDD3AB49B4177]", "D3D0400D4BCDFD8291C59687D2D019F8", "Esteemed Residents of Padstow,

We bring tidings of great import: the forthcoming election to select our esteemed Elder shall transpire in the Village of Bradford. Among the contenders for this illustrious role stands our current Elder, Patryk Sten, renowned for his valor and sagacity.

It behooves us all to be apprised of this momentous event unfolding in Bradford. Your awareness of this significant happening is crucial for the harmony and prosperity of our region.

The decisions made may greatly impact our reality, and your understanding of this pivotal event is paramount for our collective well-being.

Let us band together in spreading this missive across The Lowlands, ensuring that every soul is enlightened regarding this consequential decision that shall shape the destiny of our beloved land.

In unity,
The Council of Great Lord Ashbourne.")

data.Title: NSLOCTEXT("[017996BCEDD00E61F1F1B26AE9122FE0]", "4E0DB80E4A879560198D1CB0C9C6ED8C", "Dead or Alive")
data.Description:
NSLOCTEXT("[017996BCEDD00E61F1F1B26AE9122FE0]", "09920C1749B4452F187D0FAE86ED9D1C", "Attention, brave citizens!

A shadow stalks our land, known only as THE BUTCHER. This nefarious fiend strikes fear into the hearts of all, for he is not only dangerous but delights in the abduction of innocent villagers.

His presence is a blight upon our realm, his actions a stain upon our honor. With each disappearance, his cruelty knows no bounds, leaving families torn apart and communities in anguish.

Stay vigilant, dear citizens, and report any sightings of THE BUTCHER to the authorities. Together, we must stand united against this vile predator and ensure the safety of our people.

By decree of the crown and Lord Ashbourne. Dead or alive, THE BUTCHER needs to be punished.")

data.Title: NSLOCTEXT("[1D7D1CDE9AD81277F286E76695560786]", "14B3A3184381BA6C40620098FC31B853", "Goods For Better Future")
data.Description:
NSLOCTEXT("[1D7D1CDE9AD81277F286E76695560786]", "D9B4D96A4B4E468E19C2B686163C70E0", "Esteemed denizens of Padstow,

By the decree of the Council of Great Lord Ashbourne, we announce an adjustment in tax rates, effective immediately, to fortify the prosperity of our esteemed lumbering village. The revenues gathered shall be dedicated to the enhancement of our forestry infrastructure, vital for the sustenance of our timber-centric community.

The levied funds shall be channeled towards the maintenance and expansion of logging roads, the acquisition of advanced tools to heighten efficiency, and the establishment of educational endeavors to ensure the enduring sustainability of our timber trade. Your cooperation in fulfilling these tax obligations, tailored to the advancement of our forestry domain, is indispensable for the continual prosperity and security of Padstow.

Rest assured, every contribution shall be judiciously employed to meet the specific needs of our village, fostering a brighter future for all who partake in the noble craft of lumberjacking.

In unity,
The Council of Great Lord Ashbourne.")

data.Title: NSLOCTEXT("[6B667DA68359F588122262B494ED49DF]", "6498BAAD4AFFD8A6DC45EE95DD763C60", "Amari")
data.Description:
NSLOCTEXT("[6B667DA68359F588122262B494ED49DF]", "F62D80E245C43F194C3A3BADB2DA46D1", "Amari, a priestess of Zlytos, the god of wind, whose calm presence guided the Halmare Isles through turbulent times. She served King Falsgardus, offering guidance during invasions and periods of instability.

Known for her divination powers, she was said to read the winds of change and foresee threats before they arose, allowing the king to act decisively. Her devotion to Zlytos, a god of motion, tempests, and transformation, mirrored her ability to anticipate change and shape events with subtle influence.

To the people of the isles, she remains a symbol of wisdom, foresight, and the quiet power of counsel in times of uncertainty.")

data.Title: NSLOCTEXT("[97A9CDC3F5C75CF3538C088B7EBF9098]", "9868297D471C70BF0A5F6AA99585BFC6", "Cragkeep Castle Coffin")
data.Description: NSLOCTEXT("[97A9CDC3F5C75CF3538C088B7EBF9098]", "A7E194C947202D9CA7F7F8BBF05CEA4E", "King Falsgardus, the ruler who forged the legendary Falsgar, an elite military faction designed to protect the kingdom from powerful neighbors. Under his command, the Falsgar were trained in a secluded mountain fortress, stripped of their former lives, and pushed to the limits of their bodies and minds.\r\n\r\nThough the Falsgar became a symbol of fear and respect, time and peace eroded their prestige. As fewer recruits endured the harsh training, the faction gradually became a refuge for criminals, deserters, and the unwanted, its legendary reputation giving way to whispers of its decline. He was a king who built his legacy on discipline, sacrifice, and the unyielding resolve of his chosen warriors.")

data.Title: NSLOCTEXT("[4245B000137EB6C30D19039633090117]", "26317A314C28037D6A04868C9041B960", "Weskeras")
data.Description: NSLOCTEXT("[4245B000137EB6C30D19039633090117]", "997EED49412B97058E18199C33304F96", "This statue honors Weskeras, the founder of Rustshore, whose presence was as fearsome as the ram horns he wore into battle. Once a warrior and leader, he donned the horns to intimidate enemies and command respect on the battlefield.\r\n\r\nOver time, his deeds became legend among the Halmayans, and the settlement he established grew into the village now known as Rustshore. To this day, the statue stands as a symbol of courage, cunning, and the enduring spirit of the Halmayans who call the Rustshore and the Halmare isles home.")

data.Title: NSLOCTEXT("[3B36E246559676F15626E4D1786CDCB7]", "9CCF310545108ED8E87D1480425764FB", "Wind God Shrine")
data.Description:
NSLOCTEXT("[3B36E246559676F15626E4D1786CDCB7]", "E7651A714FFC5B0FA28B0B92AF3F7149", "Zlytos, Master of the winds, greets you.
The winds shall whisper, soft and sweet,
Of place where the gold and sea meet
There lies the treasure, still and pure,
Guarded by winds and waves secure.")

data.Title: NSLOCTEXT("[E8EE8499C10AA7FAF10E21EEA819B619]", "E3435DCA41A110E5546448AD42FC5A29", "Wine God Shrine")
data.Description:
NSLOCTEXT("[E8EE8499C10AA7FAF10E21EEA819B619]", "C3D3A3CC451C2AD7ACF30FA2226E3691", "Sorwynn, Master of Revelry, welcomes you.
From feast to flame and shattered cheer,
Where laughter fades but echoes near,
Where debauchery, breeze and tide entwine,
There awaits a prize for the bold and wise.")

data.Title: NSLOCTEXT("[D0C368F3FB2970F39F485761E6DC1271]", "4163BABB4D936D6BBDAE9193FC05C811", "Knowledge books")
data.Description:
NSLOCTEXT("[D0C368F3FB2970F39F485761E6DC1271]", "C04B28D442AB0379EE1E1A8F1509EC73", "These books contain valuable knowledge. Use it to expand your own abilities (P), or those of your settlers in the inspect screen. They can greatly improve skill mastery, but more advanced books require sufficient knowledge to learn from them.

Novice - Can be read by at any skill level
Beginner - Above level 3
Competent - Above level 5
Proficient - Above level 7
Master - Above level 9")

data.Title: NSLOCTEXT("[58535BB46168D8C64E6162FB10FA880E]", "2AFD861B4AD524F3E436F4BAEA0D67A9", "Seeds")
data.Description: NSLOCTEXT("[58535BB46168D8C64E6162FB10FA880E]", "02C457D54D6528055F3E5E93D2A7BB06", "Seeds serve as the foundational element for cultivating a variety of plants within the game. Players can acquire seeds either through the act of harvesting, where they are collected alongside the plants, or by purchasing them directly from Herbalists. These seeds are essential for players looking to engage in agriculture, allowing for the growth of diverse flora that can be used for various purposes within the game world.")
